about.summary: Simple wrapper for hyperopt to do convenient hyperparameter optimization for Keras models.

name: hyperas
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "hyperas" %}
{% set version = "0.4.1" %}

package:
  name: "{{ name|lower }}"
  version: "{{ version }}"

source:
  url: "https://github.com/maxpumperla/hyperas/archive/{{ version }}.tar.gz"
  sha256: "1165c698704f241c6627bb118b8c526f27f63762ee1d24af62cc3fb691e1c8fb"

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv"

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - python
    - setuptools
    - entrypoints
    - hyperopt
    - jupyter
    - keras
    - nbconvert
    - nbformat
  run:
    - entrypoints
    - hyperopt
    - jupyter
    - keras
    - nbconvert
    - nbformat
    - python

test:
  imports:
    - hyperas

about:
  home: "http://github.com/maxpumperla/hyperas"
  license: "MIT"
  license_family: "MIT"
  license_file: "LICENSE"
  summary: "Simple wrapper for hyperopt to do convenient hyperparameter optimization for Keras models."
  dev_url: "http://github.com/maxpumperla/hyperas"

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - marcelotrevisani
    - Tata17
